moan.translation[0].definitions[0].defin: to complain in an annoying way, especially in an unhappy voice and without good reason
moan.translation[0].definitions[0].examp: He moaned and groaned all the way there.
A lot of people moaned about the parking problems.
My mum never stops moaning at me.
He’s always moaning that we use too much electricity.
moan.translation[0].definitions[1].defin: to make a long low sound expressing pain, unhappiness, or sexual pleasure
moan.translation[0].definitions[1].examp: She moaned and cried out in pain.
moan.translation[0].definitions[2].defin: if the wind moans, it makes a long low sound
moan.translation[0].definitions[2].examp: They could hear the wind moaning in the trees.
moan.translation[1].definitions[0].defin: a long low sound expressing pain, unhappiness, or sexual pleasure
moan.translation[1].definitions[0].examp: There was a moan of pain from the injured man.
She gave a little moan of pleasure.
moan.translation[1].definitions[1].defin: a low sound made by the wind
